The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science related to algorithms and complexity theory. Specifically, the paper focuses on upper bounds on deterministic communication complexity, which is a subfield of communication complexity. The use of rank and corruption bound in the paper suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also uses tools related to data structures and algorithms, which may place it in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with combinatorial objects such as matrices, which may suggest that it belongs to the sub-categories of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
